Police have arrested a 23-year-old man in Lavender Hill for the illegal possession of a rifle. CAPE TOWN - Police have arrested a 23-year-old man in Lavender Hill for the illegal possession of a rifle.The police's Frederick Van Wyk says the suspect was nabbed on Monday following a tip-off. Upon arrival, police observed a male as per description received. When he saw the police members he started to run, police chased after him and found him to be in possession of a rifle. Meanwhile, also in Lavender Hill on Monday officers stormed a house at Van Der Leur Court, where they discovered a stash of tik and mandrax tablets.#sapsWC 49yr-old Arrested at Van Der Leur Court, Lavender Hill after drugs found on premises. #DrugsOffTheStreets MEhttps://t.co/BcNie7YZLu pic.twitter.com/KgPH9mQGQbA 49-year-old man was arrested and is expected to appear in court soon.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)